    color: "",
    description: "The NOCTA x Nike Zoom Drive “Summit White” is a collaboration by Drake and Nike on a crisp, white-based colorway of the retro sneaker. Before it was reissued with the help of Drake in 2024, the Nike Zoom Drive was originally designed by Tinker Hatfield and released in 1999 as part of the “Alpha Project.” Here, the “Summit White” colorway has an all-white appearance made from a combination of White and Summit White ballistic mesh, ripstop nylon, and leather. The shoe’s all-white look continues on the TPU overlays. Black pull tabs with “NOCTA” branding break up the shoe’s neutral appearance. Underfoot, visible Air cushioning in the heel completes the look. Release date: February 22, 2024",
