    description: "The Nike Kobe 6 Protro \"Italian Camo\" is the modern reissue of one of the original colorways of Kobe Bryant’s sixth signature shoe with Nike Basketball. Originally released in 2011, the Nike Kobe 6 Protro “Italian Camo” pays tribute to Italy’s basketball legacy as well as Kobe’s father Joe Bryant’s status as a former Italian Basketball League player. The shoe was brought back in 2024. As for its design, the upper has a camouflage pattern on its reptilian-inspired upper that is influenced by Italy’s landscape, including its vineyards, mountains, and coastlines. A Crimson Red textured Swoosh appears on both sides of the shoe, matching the fiery look of Kobe’s signature branding on the tongue. Release date: April 13, 2024",
