    description: "The Nike Air More Uptempo “Primary Colors” is a clean look for the retro performance basketball shoe that features primary colors around its iconic branding. The former signature shoe of Basketball Hall of Famer Scottie Pippen in 1996, the Air More Uptempo is a throwback to the chunky, bold, and in-your-face styling of Nike’s old school basketball shoes from the ‘90s. The model’s signature “AIR” letters on the side are designed in black leather and feature yellow, blue, and red trim around the “A,” “I,” and “R” on the lateral side of the left shoe. The colors are reversed on the lateral side of the right shoe, with red around the “A,” blue around the “I,” and yellow around the “R.” A black Swoosh appears on the toe and a jeweled white Swoosh is found on the heel. Visible Air bubbles in the white rubber midsole complete the look. Release date: December 1, 2021",
