    color: "",
    description: "The Why So Sad? x Nike SB Dunk Low is a special collaboration between pro skater John Rattray’s mental health initiative and Nike SB on the classic skate shoe. Rattray, an advocate for mental health, started his “Why So Sad?” campaign as a way to raise awareness for suicide prevention in skateboarding and beyond. His take on the SB Dunk aims to open up the conversation about the importance of mental health in skateboarding. The shoe features a Coastal Blue leather base that’s contrasted with dark blue leather overlays and Swoosh branding, both of which feature a tear-away design that reveals yellow accenting after significant wear. An embroidered logo of a bird is found on the lateral side of the heel. Yellow “Nike SB Dunk Low Pro” insignia is found on the red nylon tongue tag. A yellow question mark is embroidered on the red suede heel tab. Underfoot, a white rubber midsole and icy blue translucent outsole complete the look. Release date: November 4, 2022",
