    color: "",
    description: "The Travis Scott x Nike Mac Attack is a collaboration by the acclaimed hip-hop artist on the classic tennis and lifestyle sneaker. Originally designed for tennis star John McEnroe in the mid-1980s, the Mac Attack was one of the brand’s first tennis sneakers to achieve mainstream success upon its debut. The old school shoe was brought back by Nike in 2023 for the first time as a retro release. Here, Travis Scott adds his signature design aesthetic to the silhouette, giving it a refreshingly modern look. The shoe has a Light Smoke Grey mesh base on the sides with tonal leather overlays. The toe is finished in black mesh to match the color of the backwards leather Swoosh. A black “Cactus Jack” logo is embroidered on the heel below the grey “Nike” branding on the back of the black leather collar. The shoe’s signature checkerboard patterned logo tag appears on the tongue.",
